Source: Leung Cho Pan ©  123RF.comAccording to aReit, potential investors will benefit from strategic investments it intends to make over the next three years in the health and leisure sectors as it capitalises on the recovery of this segment in the aftermath of the Covid-19 pandemic. Other sectors will also be considered, with the main focus on strong tenants.aReit is trading under the JSE code APO with AcaciaCap Advisors as its sponsor. There are 100 million aREIT shares listed.Valdene Reddy, JSE’s director of capital markets, welcomed aReit’s listing, the second for 2022, adding that it comes at a time when South Africa’s economy, and the property sector, in particular, are gradually recovering from the Covid-19 impact.